<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1649,1746]" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">
This genus has previously included the single species 
<taxonomicName authority="Okajima. This" authorityName="Okajima. This" box="[765,1027,1649,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Siamothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argus">
<emphasis box="[765,857,1650,1673]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">S. argus</emphasis>
Okajima. This
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<specimenCount box="[1264,1387,1649,1674]" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" type="female">
<number box="[1264,1292,1650,1674]" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" value="78.0">78</number>
females
</specimenCount>
and nine males taken on 
<taxonomicName box="[391,621,1685,1709]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="4" pageNumber="391" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="melongena">
<emphasis box="[391,621,1685,1709]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">Solanum melongena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
leaves in 
<collectingCountry box="[741,844,1685,1710]" name="Thailand" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. A second species is described below, based on six females collected in Perak, Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[585,691,1721,1746]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="391">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
